Even if the meridional flow is too slow—or the turbulent magnetic diffusivity too high—to force the dynamo model in the advection-dominated regime, being much faster at the surface the poleward flow can dominate the spatio-temporal evolution of the radial surface magnetic field. For the dynamo solutions of Fig. 10, at low circulation speeds (Rm≲50\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
