An important feature of solar cycle models based on the Babcock–Leighton mechanism is that the two substeps of the dynamo loop are segregated spatially; the P→T\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
