A noteworthy property of this class of model is the dependency of the cycle period on model parameters; in the advection dominated regime, the meridional flow speed is found to be the primary determinant of the cycle period P. For example, in the Dikpati and Charbonneau (1999) model, this quantity is found to scale as51P=56.8u0-0.89s0-0.13ηT0.22[years].\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
