With downward turbulent pumping now the primary mechanism linking the surface and tachocline, the dynamo period loses sensitivity to the meridional flow speeds, and becomes set primary by the radial pumping speed. Indeed the dynamo solutions presented Guerrero and de Gouveia Dal Pino (2008) are found to obey a scaling law of the form52P=181.2u0-0.12γr0-0.51γθ0-0.05[years],\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
